    <name>Pro Tips: Learning that Works for All</name>
    <intro>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/octae-icon-protips.png" alt="" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle"&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(73, 80, 87); font-size: 1.7rem; font-family: &amp;quot;Source Sans Pro&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ol role="list" start="1"&gt;&lt;li data-charcodes="65533,0,46" data-buautonum="8" data-margin="550" data-aria-posinset="1" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{83}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:550,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-540,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}" data-indent="-540"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use case studies in your instruction:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;To introduce an instructional topic, adults will be more&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;engaged by relevant situations (cases) they can&amp;nbsp;relate to, analyze (study) and then apply. As real-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;life examples, case&amp;nbsp;studies increase relevance, value, and authenticity in learning (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank"&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/relevance-value-authenticity" target="_blank"&gt;Checkpoint 7.2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-charcodes="65533,0,46" data-buautonum="8" data-margin="550" data-aria-posinset="2" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{86}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:550,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-540,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}" data-indent="-540"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use prompts or sentence-starters:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Prompts help learners make sense of&amp;nbsp;the lesson, offering&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;learners a strategy for purposeful reflection.&amp;nbsp; Providing prompts increases engagement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;by&amp;nbsp;reducing the threats and distractions learners can feel when faced with open-ended&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;questions&amp;nbsp;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank"&gt;Engagement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/threats-distractions" target="_blank"&gt;Checkpoint 7.3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-charcodes="65533,0,46" data-buautonum="8" data-margin="550" data-aria-posinset="2" role="listitem" data-aria-level="1"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{86}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:550,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-540,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}" data-indent="-540"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p dir="ltr"&gt;&lt;span&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use video&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9660@$&amp;amp;forceview=1"&gt;:&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Videos reduce learning inequalities by removing barriers for learners that&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;struggle with text dense content. Videos provide alternative means of representation. Using video&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;increases accessibility, clarity, and comprehension for learners (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation" target="_blank"&gt;Representation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation/language-symbols/illustrate-multimedia" target="_blank"&gt;Checkpoint 2.5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;). To get the most out of video content:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul role="list"&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="1" role="listitem" data-aria-level="2"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{111}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-282,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:0}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Keep videos short (2:30 minutes to 3:30 minutes)&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="2" role="listitem" data-aria-level="2"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{114}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-282,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:0}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Always have captions on&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="3" role="listitem" data-aria-level="2"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{117}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-282,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:0}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Use signaling to highlight important ideas or concepts&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="4" role="listitem" data-aria-level="2"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{120}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-282,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:0}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Use guiding questions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li data-aria-posinset="5" role="listitem" data-aria-level="2"&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{a908f5f2-fbf8-47a6-898b-1d0a3a3b0392}{123}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:720,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-282,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.13999,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Integrate discussion questions&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use metaphors and analogies&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Adult learners bring a rich array of life experiences into the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;classroom. Analogies and metaphors are useful strategies for framing information and encouraging&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;adult learners to imagine the world in new ways, bringing together reasoning and imagination.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;Metaphors and analogies can help learners comprehend concepts and improve their ability to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;access prior knowledge in nonthreatening ways&amp;nbsp; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation" target="_blank"&gt;Representation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/representation/comprehension/transfer-generalization" target="_blank"&gt;Checkpoint 3.4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider-wave-1.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
